cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CVPR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with visual odometry using optical flow and depth information. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as visual odometry is an important component of robot navigation. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is likely as the paper proposes a deep neural network architecture for predicting scene motion. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper deals with developing an AI system for estimating scene motion. 
5. cs.CVPR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is another possible category as the paper deals with visual odometry and proposes a novel network architecture.
